==Finnish==

===Etymology===
Probably from ''[[erä]]''.

===Pronoun===
'''eräs'''

# [[certain]], [[someone]]
# [[one]]

====Synonyms====
*(''certain''): [[tietty]]
*(''one''): [[yksi]]

====Usage====
*''Eräs'' is used attributively with the sense "one" but can stand alone for "someone".
*Formerly the prescribed usage was to use ''eräs'' only for people or things the listener doesn't know. This has been relaxed officially in the recent years.

